description.narrative:
1. National policy and regulatory framework providing comprehensive and consistent support for Community Conservation Areas;
2. Area protected under Community Conservation Areas (CCA);
3. Quality of biodiversity management of CCAs as measured by Management Effectiveness Tracking Tool;
4. Landowner commitment to CCAs;
5. Funding for conservation and management of CCAs is sufficient to underwrite core activities and is sustainable over time.

comment.narrative:
No policy and legislative framework on Protected Areas. Protected Areas were established under a range of secondary legislation administered by DEC, with nil government support.
only 5 existing gazetted protected areas or 25760 hectares within the project site in New Britain Island, namely Tavolo Wildlife Mgt. Area (2,000 ha), Kavakuna WMA (20 ha), Klampun WMA (5,200 ha), Pokili WMA (9,840 ha) and garu WMA (8,700 ha); 
Database on protected areas in PNG was non-existent;
DEC stalled with approving new gazettal due to ICAD experience in 1998 where the Department declared a protection area with existing logging concession.
